Have a few things here:

  1. plots
  2. linear model (dropping mixed terms)
  3. mean subtracted

ADI plots

First, we consider boxplot of adi by weeks premature status

Or even distribution of ADI by preterm status. Noteably, the IQR of the regular term is slightly wider

In terms of these two groups, though, its also worth noting that there is not much difference in terms of thickness. Here is the distribution of thickness values with regular term in the first column, and broken down by weeks in the remaining ones

Two more plots to consider. First, we have distribution of ADI by parent education (this is highest parent ed, rather than mean education)

However, in terms of thickness (for all sites) the groups are virtually indistinguishable

Statistics for regions

Summaries

Presented here are two sets of ADI models

  1. The first is standard mixed model, the second is simple linear regression (no random terms)
  2. Adi has been replaced with adi_m, not standardized, but has the mean value subtracted (so mean is zero)
